---
metadata: {
    partial_name: 'Ecommerce | Products | Tag Chip'
}
---
{% comment %}
    A single highlighted tag chip. Colour is driven by a slugified modifier
    class (tag-chip--{slug}) so each known tag type maps to a semantic colour in
    ecommerce.css (New Arrival = success, Sale = error, Staff Pick = warning-hover,
    etc.). Unknown tags fall back to the base chip colour. Any tag whose label
    contains "sale" (e.g. "Flash Sale") uses the sale colour.

    Params:
    - tag : the tag label string (e.g. "New Arrival")
{% endcomment %}
{%- assign tag_lower = tag | downcase -%}
{%- assign tag_slug = tag_lower | strip | replace: ' ', '-' -%}
{%- comment -%} Any tag containing the word "sale" (e.g. "Flash Sale") takes the sale colour. {%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign tag_color_class = 'tag-chip--' | append: tag_slug -%}
{%- if tag_lower contains 'sale' -%}
    {%- assign tag_color_class = 'tag-chip--sale' -%}
{%- endif -%}
<ins-tag label="{{ tag }}" class="tag-chip {{ tag_color_class }}"></ins-tag>
